</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="9983A9D91B09FFC5FCBEF8D8FBA2FAE0" pageId="23" pageNumber="534" type="distribution">
<caption id="85E6AADA1B09FFC5FCBEF8D8FBA2FAE0" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6588326" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6588326" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6588326/files/figure.png" inLine="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="534" targetBox="[196,786,919,1332]" targetPageId="23">
<paragraph id="D126FA521B09FFC5FCBEF8D8FBA2FAE0" blockId="23.[810,1404,913,1340]" pageId="23" pageNumber="534">
<emphasis id="E3ED26401B09FFC5FCBEF8D8FC4AFB1A" bold="true" box="[810,986,1193,1222]" pageId="23" pageNumber="534">Distribution.</emphasis>
CW Argentina (N Neuquén Province), known only from the type locality and neighboring areas in the Chos Malal Department.
</paragraph>
</caption>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="9983A9D91B09FFC5FF52F933FBB5F9A9" pageId="23" pageNumber="534" type="description">
<paragraph id="D126FA521B09FFC5FF52F933FBB5F9A9" blockId="23.[195,1402,1346,1968]" pageId="23" pageNumber="534">
<emphasis id="E3ED26401B09FFC5FF52F933FE53FABF" bold="true" box="[198,451,1346,1379]" pageId="23" pageNumber="534">Descriptive notes.</emphasis>
Head-body 211 mm, tail 91 mm, hindfoot 39 mm (all measurements from the holotype). No specific data are available for body weight. Emilio’s Tuco-tuco is large-sized. Color is generally pale glossy fawn above, uniform on head and dorsal region; sides and venter, including chin and throat, are buffy white. This color extends to hips and thighs more than in most other species of tuco-tucos, differing noticeably from brown rump. Tail is also buffy whitish, lacking any darkening of terminal tuft. Skull is slight and flat, with low braincase and well-defined masseteric and lambdoidal ridges, and bullae are large and well inflated.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="9983A9D91B09FFC5FF51FA0DFC68F941" box="[197,1016,1660,1693]" pageId="23" pageNumber="534" type="biology_ecology">
